refentry.refsect1:
&ref.title.note;
The <project> tag also is the root tag in build files. It contains the name, the directory, a short description and a default target.
Project may contain task calls and targets (see below).

&ref.title.attributes;


  &taskAttributes.table.titlesLine.all;




      basedir



      String


    The base directory of the project, i.e. the directory all paths
    are relative to.

    &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

    &attributes.required.yes;





      default



      String


    The name of the target that is executed if none is explicitely
    specified when calling Phing

    all

    &attributes.required.no;





      description



      String


    A free text description of the project

    &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

    &attributes.required.no;





      name



      String


    Name of the project

    &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

    &attributes.required.yes;
